# Cloudflare Pages headers config. One rule per block, path + indented
# header lines. Glob '*' supported.
#
# Strategy: 'no-store' on every asset. The browser never writes the
# response to disk and the bfcache is bypassed, so a plain reload (or
# even a back/forward navigation) always fetches the live deploy.
# Trade-off vs. 'max-age=0, must-revalidate': we lose the 304 short
# circuit, so every visit re-downloads the full payload. data.json is
# ~1.5 MB and data-blobs.json ~8 MB; the latter is lazy-loaded on
# first place detail. If file size becomes a concern, switch to
# 304-style caching once data.json content settles.

/*.html
  Cache-Control: no-store

/*.json
  Cache-Control: no-store

/*.js
  Cache-Control: no-store

/*.css
  Cache-Control: no-store

# Security headers — site is read-only static, no auth, no forms.
#
# CSP notes:
# - No remote scripts in v1 (no Leaflet, no analytics).
# - style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' — index.html / app.js use a
#   handful of inline style="…" attributes for one-off layout touches.
#   Accepted: CSS-only XSS has very limited impact on a read-only
#   site without auth.
# - img-src 'self' data: — favicon is an inline SVG data: URI.
# - connect-src 'self' — only fetches are data.json + data-blobs.json
#   from the same origin.
# - External Internet Archive, NGIB, Wikipedia and sibling-site links
#   are navigational (<a href>), not embedded resources, so they don't
#   need CSP allowances.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), interest-cohort=()
